StudyInfo.StudyNameEntrez: A Genomic Approach to Warfarin Dose Prescription in Admixed Caribbean Hispanics

Policy.acknowledgement_statement: This material is the result of work supported with resources and the use of facilities at the Veterans Affairs Caribbean Healthcare System (VACHS) in San Juan, Puerto Rico. This work has been supported by the grant SC1 HL123911 from the National Institutes of Health (NIH), National Heart, Lung, and Blood Institute (NHLBI) and the Minority Biomedical Research Support-Support of Competitive Research (MBRS-SCORE) Program of the NIH, National Institute of General Medical Sciences (NIGMS). Part of this research has been funded by the Research Minority Institutions (RCMI) award G12 MD007600 from the NIH, National Institute on Minority Health and Health Disparities (NIMHD) and by the Minority Biomedical Research Support-Research Initiative for Scientific Enhancement (MBRS-RISE) at the University of Puerto Rico Medical Sciences Campus (UPR MSC) with the grant R25 GM061838 from the NIH, National Institute of General Medical Sciences (NIGMS). For details on the origin of the dataset, please consult the following publication: PMC5461284; doi:10.3389/fphar.2017.00347.
